This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category since it proposes an alternative neural network structure to overcome the vanishing gradient problem. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category since it discusses the training of neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) since neural networks are a popular tool in AI research. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is another possible sub-category since neural networks are widely used in image recognition tasks. Finally, it could be categorized under Signal Processing (cs.SI) since neural networks are used in various signal processing applications.
